#    paths). Those will require either (a) additional input signals
#    propagated into the Early Builder, or (b) a second audit-stamp node
#    inserted after each upstream terminator. To be sequenced after this
#    initial fix is verified live.
# 2. UNKNOWN-3 dead-code cleanup at L136–L141 (the unused riskGateStatus
#    branch) is intentionally NOT in this diff. Per user instruction, leave
#    intact for provenance; remove as a separate follow-up.
# 3. The new value `RISK_NOT_REACHED` is a new audit enum value. No DB
#    consumer references the column (see UNKNOWN-2 in section_3_report.md).
